  "prompt": "Where can I get an explainer video for $100?",
  "response": "Finding a high-quality explainer video for $100 can be challenging, as professional video production services often charge more. However, there are a few options you can explore to get an explainer video within your budget:\n\n1. **Freelance Platforms:**\n   - **Fiverr:** You might find freelancers who offer basic explainer video services starting at around $100. Be sure to check their reviews and portfolio to ensure quality.\n   - **Upwork:** While many freelancers on Upwork charge more, you can sometimes find someone willing to work within your budget, especially if it's a simple project.\n\n2. **Template-Based Services:**\n   - **Canva:** Canva offers customizable video templates that you can use to create your own explainer video. While not professionally produced, it\u2019s a cost-effective option.\n   - **Animaker:** This platform provides a range of templates and allows you to create animated videos. They have a free tier, and paid plans start at a reasonable rate.\n\n3. **Crowdsourcing:**\n   - **99designs:** This platform sometimes runs contests where multiple designers submit their work, and you choose the winner. You might be able to find a good deal if you specify your budget.\n\n4. **Students and New Professionals:**\n   - **Local Colleges and Universities:** Reach out to the media or design departments at nearby colleges. Students often look for real-world projects to build their portfolios and might work within your budget.\n\n5. **DIY Software:**\n   - **Powtoon:** Offers a free trial and affordable plans that allow you to create your own explainer videos using their templates and tools.\n   - **Biteable:** Another user-friendly platform where you can create videos using pre-made templates.\n\nWhen commissioning a video for $100, be prepared for a simpler product. You might need to compromise on aspects like length, complexity, or customization. Always review portfolios and discuss your needs clearly with the freelancer or service to ensure you get the best possible outcome within your budget.",
